collect(bool,bool,uint256,bytes).details: User have both options whether to recieve fees in PILOT or in pool token0 & token1

params.data: Necessary data needed to collect fees from Unipilot
params.pilotToken: whether to recieve fees in PILOT or not (valid if user is not reciving fees in token0, token1)
params.tokenId: The ID of the Unpilot NFT for which tokens will be collected
params.wethToken: whether to recieve fees in WETH or ETH (only valid for WETH/ALT pairs)

params._token0: The contract address of token0 of the pool
params._token1: The contract address of token1 of the pool
params.data: Necessary data needed to create pool In data we will provide the `fee` amount of the v3 pool for the specified token pair, also `sqrtPriceX96` The initial square root price of the pool

returns._pool: Returns the pool address based on the pair of tokens and fee, will return the newly created pool address

params.amount0Desired: Max amount of token0 to deposit
params.amount1Desired: Max amount of token1 to deposit
params.isTokenMinted: Boolean to check the minting of new tokenId of Unipilot
params.token0: The first of the two tokens of the pool, sorted by address
params.token1: The second of the two tokens of the pool, sorted by address

getReserves(address,address,bytes).details: Updates the position and return the latest reserves & liquidity.

params.data: any necessary data needed to get reserves

returns.totalAmount0: Amount of token0 in the pool of unipilot
returns.totalAmount1: Amount of token1 in the pool of unipilot
returns.totalLiquidity: Total liquidity available in unipilot pool

returns._0: LiquidityPosition - baseTickLower The lower tick of the base position - baseTickUpper The upper tick of the base position - baseLiquidity The total liquidity of the base position - rangeTickLower The lower tick of the range position - rangeTickUpper The upper tick of the range position - rangeLiquidity The total liquidity of the range position - fees0 Total amount of fees collected by unipilot positions in terms of token0 - fees1 Total amount of fees collected by unipilot positions in terms of token1 - feeGrowthGlobal0 The fee growth of token0 collected per unit of liquidity for the entire life of the unipilot vault - feeGrowthGlobal1 The fee growth of token1 collected per unit of liquidity for the entire life of the unipilot vault - totalLiquidity Total amount of liquidity of vault including base & range orders

uniswapV3MintCallback(uint256,uint256,by.details: In the implementation you must pay to the pool for the minted liquidity.

params.amount0Owed: The amount of token0 due to the pool for the minted liquidity
params.amount1Owed: The amount of token1 due to the pool for the minted liquidity
params.data: Any data passed through by the caller via the IUniswapV3PoolActions#mint call

uniswapV3SwapCallback(int256,int256,byte.details: In the implementation you must pay to the pool for swap.

params.amount0Delta: The amount of token0 due to the pool for the swap
params.amount1Delta: The amount of token1 due to the pool for the swap
params.data: Any data passed through by the caller via the IUniswapV3PoolActions#swap call

returns.amount0: Total amount of token0 in vault
returns.amount1: Total amount of token1 in vault

params.tokenId: The ID of the token that represents the position

returns._0: Position - nonce The nonce for permits - pool Address of the uniswap V3 pool - liquidity The liquidity of the position - feeGrowth0 The fee growth of token0 as of the last action on the individual position - feeGrowth1 The fee growth of token1 as of the last action on the individual position - tokensOwed0 The uncollected amount of token0 owed to the position as of the last computation - tokensOwed1 The uncollected amount of token1 owed to the position as of the last computation

params.data: Necessary data needed to withdraw liquidity from Unipilot
params.liquidity: The amount by which liquidity will be withdrawn
params.pilotToken: whether to recieve fees in PILOT or not (valid if user is not reciving fees in token0, token1)
params.tokenId: The ID of the token for which liquidity is being withdrawn
params.wethToken: whether to recieve fees in WETH or ETH (only valid for WETH/ALT pairs)

collect(bool,bool,uint256,bytes).notice: Collects up to a maximum amount of fees owed to a specific user position to the recipient

createPair(address,address,bytes).notice: Creates a new pool & then initializes the pool

deposit(address,address,uint256,uint256,.notice: Deposits tokens in proportion to the Unipilot's current ticks, mints them `Unipilot`s NFT.

getReserves(address,address,bytes).notice: Calculates the vault's total holdings of TOKEN0 and TOKEN1 - in other words, how much of each token the vault would hold if it withdrew all its liquidity from Uniswap.

poolPositions(address).notice: Returns the vault information of unipilot base & range orders

uniswapV3MintCallback(uint256,uint256,by.notice: Pull in tokens from sender. Called to `msg.sender` after minting liquidity to a position from IUniswapV3Pool#mint.

uniswapV3SwapCallback(int256,int256,byte.notice: Called to `msg.sender` after minting swaping from IUniswapV3Pool#swap.

updatePositionTotalAmounts(address).notice: Calculates the vault's total holdings of token0 and token1 - in other words, how much of each token the vault would hold if it withdrew all its liquidity from Uniswap.

userPositions(uint256).notice: Returns the user position information associated with a given token ID.

withdraw(bool,bool,uint256,uint256,bytes.notice: withdraws the desired shares from the vault with accumulated user fees and transfers to recipient.
